Description: Handle; earthenware; from an amphopra; oval-sectioned; stamped on one side with an inscription.
Curator's comments: Cf. M. Lawall, "Hellenistic Stamped Amphora Handles", in: Forschungen in Ephesos, vol. IX/2/3 (Vienna 2007) 28-60, cat. AH25.
Previous owner: Previous owner/ex-collection: British School of Archaeology, Egypt
